You are returning `isAvailable` before the observable has completed. You need to change it so that the function returns the observable:

    get isApiAvailable(): Promise&lt;boolean&gt; {

        return this.checkIfCoreApiIsAvailable()
            .pipe(
              first(),
              map(resp  =&gt; {
                if (resp.status === 200 ) {
                  return true;
                }

                return false;
              })
            )
            .toPromise();
        }

Then you need to handle the observable response here:

    let isServiceAvailable = await this.connectionService.isApiAvailable;

Notice how I converted the observable to a promise so that you can use `await` without having to change too much of your code. Make sure to prepend the `checkLogin` function with the `async` keyword or using `await` will throw error.

If you don&#39;t want to use a promise you can simply tweak the code to listen for the observable response instead.

